14_ImportsByBEC.Economic Category: TRANSPORT EQUIPMENT AND PARTS AND ACCESSORIES THEREOF
1  Capital Goods: sum of categories 41* and 521*
2  Intermediate Goods: sum of categories 111*, 121*, 21*, 22*, 31*, 322*, 42* and 53*
3  Consumption Goods: sum of categories 112*, 122*, 522*, 61*, 62* and 63*

The BEC serves as a means for converting retained import data into end use categories that are meaningful within the framework of the System of National Accounts. Except categories 321* and 51* which are used extensively namely capital goods, both for industry and for household consumption and category 7* which includes a range of commodities, the correspondence of the 16 remaining BEC basic categories with the  basic classes of goods in the SNA are:
1  Capital Goods: sum of categories 41* and 521*
2  Intermediate Goods: sum of categories 111*, 121*, 21*, 22*, 31*, 322*, 42* and 53*
3  Consumption Goods: sum of categories 112*, 122*, 522*, 61*, 62* and 63*
4 This table is compiled on an annual basis since the National Accounts statistics in Vanuatu are compiled on an annual basis.

* The asterisk follows each reference to a BEC classification as a device to avoid confusion with the numbered sections, divisions and groups of the standard international trade classification, revision 4.
